\'93Hurry up, you useless children, my shame.\uc0\u8232 I wish you\'92d all been killed instead of Hector\u8232 by those swift ships\'97the entire bunch of you!\u8232 My life\'92s so miserable and empty.\u8232 I fathered sons, the best in spacious Troy.\u8232 I don\'92t think a single one of them is left\'97\u8232 not Mestor, or horseman Troilus, or Hector,\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0320\u8232 that god among men. He didn\'92t seem to be\u8232 the child of any mortal man, but of a god.\u8232 Ares destroyed all those sons of mine.\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0[260]\u8232 The ones still left here are disgraceful\'97\u8232 liars, prancing masters of the dance floor,\u8232 who steal lambs and goats from their own people.\u8232 Will you not prepare a wagon for me\'97\u8232 and quickly? Put all those items in it,\u8232 so we can start out on our way.\'94\
\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0Priam finished.\uc0\u8232 The sons, shaken by their father\'92s torrent of abuse,\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0330\u8232 brought out the sturdy, well-made wagon, a new one.\u8232 They lashed the wicker basket on it, then took down\u8232 from its peg a box-wood yoke to fit a team of mules,\u8232 furnished with guiding rings and with a knob on top.\u8232 They brought out with the yoke the lashing for it,\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0[270]\u8232 a strap five metres long. They placed the yoke with care\u8232 across the polished pole at its front end, then set\u8232 the rope\'92s eye on the peg and bound it up securely\u8232 with three twists round the knob. They lashed it to the pole,\u8232 twisting the end below the hook. Next, they brought out\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0340\u8232 from the storeroom and stowed in the well-polished cart\u8232 the huge ransom to be paid for Hector\'92s head. The mules\u8232 they then put into harness, underneath the yoke,\u8232 strong-footed beasts, a splendid gift which Mysians\u8232 once gave Priam. Then to Priam\'92s chariot they yoked up\u8232 the team the old man kept for his own personal use,\u8232 taking care of them in his own gleaming stables.\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0[280]\
