Hermes the Guide, killer of Argus, then replied:\
\'93You want to test me, old man, by asking me\uc0\u8232 of godlike Hector. My eyes have seen him\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0[390]\u8232 many times in fights where men win glory.\u8232 And when he drove the Argives to their ships,\u8232 killing and butchering them with his sharp bronze,\u8232 we stood there astonished. For Achilles,\u8232 still in a furious rage with Agamemnon,\u8232 would not let us fight. I attend on him.\u8232 The same ship brought us here. I\'92m a soldier,\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0490\u8232 one of the Myrmidons. My father\'92s Polyctor,\u8232 a man of substance, about as old as you.\u8232 He has six other sons\'97I\'92m the seventh.\u8232 By casting lots with them I was selected\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0[400]\u8232 to sail here. I\'92ve come now from our ships\u8232 here to the plain. At dawn bright-eyed Achaeans\u8232 will organize for battle round the city.\u8232 They\'92re restless, just sitting idly there.\u8232 And it\'92s impossible for Achaea\'92s kings\u8232 to keep in check their eagerness for war.\'94\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0500\
