Hermes the Guide, killer of Argus, answered:\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0[410]\
\'93Old man, birds and dogs have not yet fed on him.\uc0\u8232 He\'92s lying still beside Achilles\'92 ship,\u8232 among the huts, the same as when he died.\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0510\u8232 For twelve days he\'92s lain there, but his flesh\u8232 has not decayed. Worms are not eating him,\u8232 as they do with men who die in battle.\u8232 Each dawn, Achilles drags him ruthlessly\u8232 around his dear companion\'92s burial mound,\u8232 but that does not lacerate the corpse.\u8232 It would amaze you, if you went in person,\u8232 to see how he lies there as fresh as dew,\u8232 with all blood washed away, no stain on him.\u8232 All the wounds he got have closed completely,\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0520\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0[420]\u8232 and many people stuck their bronze in him.\u8232 But that\'92s how blessed gods care for your son,\u8232 though he\'92s a corpse. For their hearts loved him.\'94\
