\'93My son, it\'92s good to pay immortal gods\uc0\u8232 what\'92s due to them. It\'92s certainly the case,\u8232 as true as that my son was once alive,\u8232 he never once neglected in our home\u8232 the gods who hold Olympus. That\'92s the reason\u8232 they now remember him for what he did,\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0530\u8232 even his dead body after death. Come now,\u8232 take this lovely goblet as my gift to you.\u8232 Protect me. Be my guide with the gods\'92 help,\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0[430]\u8232 until I reach the hut of Peleus\'92 son.\'94\
